===Etymology===
From {{OF.}} {{term|pourpartie||lang=fro}}, from {{term|pour||for|lang=fro}} and {{term|partie||a part|lang=fro}}. Compare {{OF.}} {{term|purpart||a respective part|lang=fro}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=purparties}}

# {{law}} A share, part, or portion of an [[estate]] allotted to a [[coparcener]].
#* '''1793''' October 6, [[w:Horace Walpole, 4th Earl of Orford|Horace Walpole]], letter to “the Miss Berrys” (sisters [[w:Mary Berry (writer)|Mary]] and Agnes Berry),<sup>[http://books.google.com/books?id=fPkDAAAAQAAJ&amp;pg=PA493&amp;dq=purparties]</sup>
#*: I am forced to eat all the game of your '''purparties''', as well as my own thirds.

